summary:
The Council also expressed its intention to consider specific action to improve implementation of and compliance with the arms embargo.
The Security Council 
1. 
Reaffirms its previous resolutions 1425 (2002), 1474 (2003), 1519 (2003), 1558 (2004), 1587 (2005), 1630 (2005), 1676 (2006), and 1724 (2006); 
2. 
Decides to establish, for a period of 6 months, a Monitoring Group, 
appointed by the Secretary-General and to be composed of 5 members, 
mandated 
 inter alia 
: 
to monitor the implementation of the 
arms embargo; 
to gather information on violations; 
to work with the Committee; 
to provide recommendations; 
3. 
Requests the Monitoring Group 
 inter alia 
: 
to work closely with the Committee; 
to identify areas to strengthen Statesâ€™ capacities; 
to provide a midterm briefing; 
to submit progress reports; 
to submit a final report; 
4. 
Requests the Secretary-General to make necessary financial arrangements; 
5. 
Reaffirms paragraphs 4, 5, 7, 8 and 10 of resolution 1519 (2003); 
6. 
Requests the Committee to consider recommendations and improve 
implementation; 
7. 
Decides to remain actively seized.
